        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 6:00PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 600 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Fairplay, or 11 miles
east of Carrollton, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Douglasville, Carrollton, City of South Fulton, Villa Rica, Powder
Springs, Austell, Palmetto, Hiram, Whitesburg, Chattahoochee Hill,
Lithia Springs, Plant Yates, Brownsville, Bill Arp, Seaton Lake,
Fairplay, Dunaway Gardens, Clem, Winston, and Lake Val-Do-Mar.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
